('NA000101', 'Quercinus', 'masculine', 'Latin adjective derived from *quercus* "oak". Rare name possibly indicating connection to oak groves or Jupiter Quercinus.', 'Quercinus', 'Quercinus', 'RR00001', 'SC00001', CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP),

('NA000102', 'Sciurinus', 'masculine', 'Roman cognomen derived from Greek *skiouros* (*σκίουρος*) "squirrel", literally "shadow-tail". Rare name possibly indicating agility or a nickname based on physical characteristics.', 'Sciurinus', 'Sciurinus', 'RR00001', 'SC00001', CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP),

('NA000103', 'Sciurius', 'masculine', 'Roman cognomen derived from Greek *skiouros* (*σκίουρος*) "squirrel", literally "shadow-tail". Variant form, possibly indicating agility or behavior reminiscent of a squirrel.', 'Sciurius', 'Sciurius', 'RR00001', 'SC00001', CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP),

('NA000104', 'Macrobius', 'masculine', 'Latin name derived from Greek *makrobios* (*μακροβίος*) "long-lived". Famous bearer: Macrobius Ambrosius Theodosius, late Roman writer.', 'Macrobius', 'Macrobius', 'RR00001', 'SC00001', CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP),

('NA000105', 'Virgil', 'masculine', 'Anglicized form of *Vergilius*. Famous bearer: Publius Vergilius Maro (Virgil), author of the *Aeneid*. Name possibly derived from *virga* "rod", "staff".', 'Virgil', 'Virgil', 'RR00001', 'SC00001', CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP),

('NA000106', 'Numa', 'masculine', 'Roman name of uncertain etymology, possibly Sabine. Famous bearer: Numa Pompilius, second legendary king of Rome, known for religious reforms and peaceful reign.', 'Numa', 'Numa', 'RR00001', 'SC00001', CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP),

('NA000107', 'Suetonius', 'masculine', 'Roman nomen of uncertain origin. Famous bearer: Gaius Suetonius Tranquillus, Roman historian and author of *The Twelve Caesars*.', 'Suetonius', 'Suetonius', 'RR00001', 'SC00001', CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP),

('NA000108', 'Varro', 'masculine', 'Roman cognomen meaning *varus* "knock-kneed" or "bow-legged". Famous bearer: Marcus Terentius Varro, scholar and author.', 'Varro', 'Varro', 'RR00001', 'SC00001', CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP),

('NA000109', 'Tullus', 'masculine', 'Roman praenomen. Famous bearer: Tullus Hostilius, third legendary king of Rome, known for militaristic reign. Etymology uncertain.', 'Tullus', 'Tullus', 'RR00001', 'SC00001', CURRENT_TIMESTAMP, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP),

